+            // Fires exactly once per loop iteration of this Execute() while
+            // loop, i.e. once per architectural instruction retired (ARM or
+            // THUMB, taken or condition-failed). A Thumb BL long branch is two
+            // separate table entries (T_BL_LONG_1/T_BL_LONG_2, one per
+            // halfword) dispatched on two separate iterations, so it retires
+            // as two instructions here — matching real ARMv5TE semantics
+            // (Thumb has no native 32-bit encoding; BL is architecturally a
+            // prefix+suffix pair). Defined in the oracle shim
+            // (oracle/shim/nds_oracle.cpp); resolved at the final link of
+            // nds_oracle. No-op in any build without the shim define.
+            // NOTE: fully qualified melonDS::NDS* — the unqualified `NDS`
+            // here would resolve to this class's `melonDS::NDS& NDS` member
+            // (see ARM.h), not the type, and silently break overload/type
+            // resolution.
+            extern void Oracle_OnInsnRetire(melonDS::NDS* nds, u32 cpu);
+            Oracle_OnInsnRetire(&NDS, Num);
+#endif
